<%# <h1>Guests#show</h1> %>
<div class="d-flex" style="position:relative">
  <span><p id="notice" style="position:absolute; top: 10px; right: 10px; background-color:rgb(165, 156, 148); color:black"><%= notice %></p></span>
  <div class="container m-0">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-3 sideImage">
      </div>
      <div class="col px-4 sideInfo">
        <h1 class="questions">Details & Questions</h1>
        <h2 class="questions">Virtual shower details:</h2>
        <p>
          Prepare your favorite tea or another drink to sip while we're together.
          Janaya's favorites are Rooibos and Chai but prepare what you'd like.<br><br>
          Dress to impress but you can still be comfortable. Most importantly, come prepared to have some fun!
          We'll play games and share stories and advice to prepare her for the little one!
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight:bold">We want to send a special gift to 10 people. Please RSVP by the 29th to be included in the drawing!</p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1571934811356-5cc061b6821f?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2067&q=80" alt="china teacup full of tea with tea leaves all around">

        <h2 class="questions">Questions</h2>
          <h3 class="topic">...about the Shower</h3>
          <ul>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> Is there a theme or dress code for the shower?</p>
          <p class="answer">No real dress code but it would be great if you dressed as if you were
          joining us in person. We'll have a little tea party. Janaya's favorite teas are
          Rooibos and Chai, but bring what you would like.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> What colors would they like for gifts?</p>
          <p class="answer">We love autumn tones - beige, burgundy, mustard yellow, forest green. Think of a beautiful fall day!<br>
          </p>
          </li>
          </ul>
          <h3 class="topic">...about the Baby</h3>
          <ul>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> Do they know the gender?</p>
          <p class="answer">Not yet, it will be a surprise! We'll all find out on the day of the birth.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> Does she want a boy or a girl?</p>
          <p class="answer">Janaya doesn't like to do hair so she'd love to have a boy!</p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> What is the due date?</p>
          <p class="answer">The little one is expected to arrive on the 22nd of June!</p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> Have they chosen a name?</p>
          <p class="answer">Not yet. It's the hardest thing - we welcome suggestions!!</p>
          </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="topic">...about the Mother-to-be</h3>
          <ul>
          <li>
          <p class="question"><i class="arrow down"></i> What does she need the most?</p>
          <p class="answer">There are items on the registry that are listed as Must-have. If you are a mother and you think of something that was not added, don't hesistate to get it.</p>
          </li>
          </ul>
           <script>
              const question = document.querySelectorAll("p.question")

              function changeDisplay(item) {
                const answer = item.nextElementSibling
                item.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
                console.log(event);
                console.log(event.currentTarget);
                if (answer.style.display === "none") {
                    answer.style.display = "block";
                    item.style.backgroundColor = "#FFFFFF";
                  } else {
                    answer.style.display = "none";
                    item.style.backgroundColor = "";
                  }
              })}
              question.forEach(changeDisplay);
            </script>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
